= Introduction =

_Youtube-upload_ is a command-line script that uploads videos to Youtube. If a video does not comply with Youtube limitations (<2Gb and <15') you must split it before using ffmpeg or any other tool. _Youtube-upload_ should work on any platform (GNU/Linux, BSD, OS X, Windows, ...) that runs Python.

= Dependencies =

  * [http://www.python.org python] (>= 2.5)
  * [http://code.google.com/p/gdata-python-client python-gdata] (>= 1.2.4)

= Download & Install =

  * [http://code.google.com/p/youtube-upload/downloads/list Stable release]:

{{{
$ wget http://youtube-upload.googlecode.com/files/youtube-upload-VERSION.tgz
$ tar xvzf youtube-upload-VERSION.tgz
$ cd youtube-upload-VERSION
$ sudo python setup.py install
}}}

  * [http://code.google.com/p/youtube-upload/source/checkout From repository]:

{{{
$ svn checkout http://youtube-upload.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ youtube-upload
$ cd youtube-upload
$ sudo python setup.py install
}}}

= Usage examples =

* Upload a small video:

{{{
$ youtube-upload myemail@gmail.com mypassword somevideo.avi "Title" "Description" "Category" "tag1, tag2"
www.youtube.com/watch?v=pxzZ-fYjeYs
}}}

* Upload a big video:

{{{
$ youtube-upload myemail@gmail.com mypassword somebigvideo.flv "Title" "Description" "Category" "tag1, tag2"
www.youtube.com/watch?v=pxzZ-fYjeYs
www.youtube.com/watch?v=fe1s43-f1f8
www.youtube.com/watch?v=9fgqref13ww
}}}

* Get available categories:

{{{
$ youtube-upload -c
Tech Education Animals People Travel Entertainment Howto Sports Autos Music News Games Nonprofit Comedy Film
}}}

If you don't want (or you can't) install software on the computer, run it directly from sources:

{{{
$ cd youtube-upload-VERSION
$ python youtube_upload/youtube_upload.py ...
}}}

* Upload with _curl_

The Youtube API does not provide any feedback on the upload process nor allow the user to tweak it (limit the speed, use a proxy, ...). Fortunately, the API does provide an alternative upload  method (a HTTP POST), so we can easily use third-party applications to do the actual upload. 

The source code includes an example ([http://code.google.com/p/youtube-upload/source/browse/trunk/examples/upload_with_curl.sh examples/upload_with_curl.sh]) that shows how to upload a video using _curl_. This command (UNIX-like operating systems only) would upload _somevideo.flv_ with a limit rate of 100KBytes (notice the _-u_ option in _youtube-upload_):

{{{
$ youtube-upload -u myemail@gmail.com mypassword somevideo.flv "Title" "Description" "Category" "tag1,tag2" |
    bash examples/upload_with_curl.sh --limit-rate 100k
}}}

